('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:mcq:63b47ff2', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "<span data-say=\"Se debe comer más fruta y verduras.\" data-listen></span><br>Listen. What is the advice?", "options": ["One should eat more fruit and vegetables", "One must not eat so much fruit or fatty food", "They always eat their fruit and vegetables first", "You have to grow your own fruit and vegetables"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘se debe comer más’ = one should eat more. Trap B flips it to a negative; C and D change the verb — you have to actually hear ‘se debe … más’."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:mcq:02bbce07', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "<span data-say=\"Voy a beber menos azúcar.\" data-listen></span><br>Listen. What does the speaker plan to do?", "options": ["Have less sugar", "Drink more sugary things", "Give up fizzy drinks completely", "Stop drinking coffee with sugar"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘voy a beber menos azúcar’ = I’m going to have less sugar. Trap B swaps menos→more; C and D add detail that was never said."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:mcq:6f0266d2', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "<span data-say=\"No se debe comer demasiada grasa.\" data-listen></span><br>Listen. Which is correct?", "options": ["One must not eat too much fat", "One should add a little healthy fat", "You are allowed to eat as much as you like", "It is fine to fry your food in lots of oil"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘no se debe comer demasiada grasa’ = one must not eat too much fat. Every distractor is longer AND reverses the meaning — you must hear the ‘no’."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:mcq:c7e8c71e', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "‘una dieta equilibrada’ means…", "options": ["a balanced diet", "a varied menu", "a healthy lifestyle", "a strict weight-loss plan"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "equilibrada = balanced. ‘variada’ (varied), ‘vida sana’ (lifestyle) and a diet-plan are close but wrong."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:mcq:9b8e8f18', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Only ONE sentence is fully correct. Which?", "options": ["Me gustan las verduras", "Me gusta las verduras", "A mí me gusta mucho las verduras", "Yo gusto las verduras todos los días"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "The thing liked is plural (verduras) so the verb is gustan. B fails to agree; C still uses gusta with a plural; D wrongly conjugates gustar as ‘yo gusto’."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:mcq:5900359d', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "How do you say ‘I am going to eat more vegetables’?", "options": ["Voy a comer más verduras", "Como muchas más verduras ahora", "Se debe comer más verduras hoy", "Voy comer más verduras cada día"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "A plan = voy a + infinitive. B is present tense; C is impersonal advice; D drops the ‘a’ that ‘voy a’ needs."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:mcq:e4486e27', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "In ‘Voy a evitar la comida rápida’, ‘evitar’ means to…", "options": ["avoid", "prepare it quickly", "cut down on it", "order it less often"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "evitar = to avoid. The longer options are tempting ‘sort of healthy’ ideas, but none means avoid."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:mcq:de4e53f3', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "‘Bebo mucha ___.’ — which word fits BOTH the grammar and ‘I drink lots of water’?", "options": ["agua", "leche", "zumo", "café con leche"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘mucha’ is feminine, so leche/agua both fit grammatically — but only ‘agua’ = water. zumo is masculine (mucho zumo)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:mcq:fb6c2008', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘because’ (gives a reason)?", "options": ["porque", "aunque", "también", "pero"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "porque = because. ‘aunque’ (although) is the closest trap; también = also; pero = but."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:mcq:c271de74', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Why is ‘Se debería reducir el azúcar’ a strong Higher-tier phrase?", "options": ["It uses the conditional", "It is in the present tense", "It gives a direct command", "It describes a completed past action"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘se debería’ = one should (conditional) — a Higher feature. The traps name other tenses/moods of similar length."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:tf:2a8da2c8', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘una dieta equilibrada’ means ‘a balanced diet’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "equilibrada = balanced."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:tf:74faf293', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘se debe’ is followed by a past-tense verb."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "It is followed by an infinitive: se debe comer / beber / evitar."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:tf:43912343', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘Me gustan las verduras’ is correct because ‘verduras’ is plural."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "gustar agrees with the thing liked; plural → gustan."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:tf:2e56aa3c', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘evitar’ means ‘to enjoy’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "evitar = to avoid."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:tf:41c7f9b4', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘voy a comer’ describes a future plan."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "voy a + infinitive = near future."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:tf:525ee299', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘el azúcar’ means ‘salt’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "el azúcar = sugar; salt = la sal."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:tf:db7ffd90', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘porque’ means ‘but’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "porque = because; ‘but’ = pero."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:tf:8b81b721', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘Se debería reducir el azúcar’ uses the conditional and suits Higher tier."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "se debería = one should (conditional)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:learn:83731027', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "What food and drink words do I need?", "reading": "<p>Start with the core nouns for <strong>la comida</strong> (food) and <strong>la bebida</strong> (drink). Every Spanish word below is on the AQA list — tap 🔊 to hear it.</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"la fruta\">la fruta</span></td><td>fruit</td><td><span data-say=\"las verduras\">las verduras</span></td><td>vegetables</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"la carne\">la carne</span></td><td>meat</td><td><span data-say=\"el pescado\">el pescado</span></td><td>fish</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"el pan\">el pan</span></td><td>bread</td><td><span data-say=\"el queso\">el queso</span></td><td>cheese</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"el agua\">el agua</span></td><td>water</td><td><span data-say=\"la leche\">la leche</span></td><td>milk</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"el azúcar\">el azúcar</span></td><td>sugar</td><td><span data-say=\"la grasa\">la grasa</span></td><td>fat</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p>Two useful meal words: <span data-say=\"el desayuno\">el desayuno</span> (breakfast) and <span data-say=\"la cena\">la cena</span> (dinner).</p>", "question": "Which pair means ‘fruit and vegetables’?", "options": ["la fruta y las verduras", "las legumbres y el pescado", "la carne y el queso", "el agua y la leche"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "la fruta = fruit, las verduras = vegetables. B mixes pulses and fish; C is meat and cheese."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:learn:18817afb', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "How do I describe a balanced diet?", "reading": "<p>The headline phrase is <span data-say=\"una dieta equilibrada\">una dieta equilibrada</span> — <em>a balanced diet</em>. Notice the adjective <strong>equilibrada</strong> agrees with the feminine noun <strong>dieta</strong>.</p>\n            <ul>\n              <li><span data-say=\"sano\">sano</span> / <span data-say=\"saludable\">saludable</span> = healthy</li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"bueno para la salud\">bueno para la salud</span> = good for your health</li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"malo para la salud\">malo para la salud</span> = bad for your health</li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>Model sentence: <span data-say=\"Como una dieta equilibrada porque es buena para la salud.\">Como una dieta equilibrada porque es buena para la salud.</span> — <em>I eat a balanced diet because it is good for your health.</em></p>", "question": "Why does ‘equilibrada’ end in ‑a?", "options": ["It agrees with the feminine noun ‘dieta’", "It must copy the last letter of the word before it", "It is a verb ending", "It marks the plural"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Adjectives agree in gender and number with their noun: dieta is feminine singular → equilibrada (not a rule about the previous word)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:learn:00ad8521', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "How do I give advice? (se debe / hay que)", "reading": "<p>To say what people <strong>should</strong> do, use these impersonal structures — each is followed by an <strong>infinitive</strong>:</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"se debe\">se debe…</span></td><td>one must / you should…</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"no se debe\">no se debe…</span></td><td>one must not…</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"hay que\">hay que…</span></td><td>you have to…</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p>Examples:</p>\n            <ul>\n              <li><span data-say=\"Se debe comer más fruta.\">Se debe comer más fruta.</span> — One should eat more fruit.</li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"No se debe comer demasiada grasa.\">No se debe comer demasiada grasa.</span> — One must not eat too much fat.</li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"Hay que beber mucha agua.\">Hay que beber mucha agua.</span> — You have to drink lots of water.</li>\n            </ul>", "question": "What kind of word follows ‘se debe’, ‘no se debe’ and ‘hay que’?", "options": ["an infinitive verb", "a fully conjugated past-tense verb", "a plural noun", "an adjective"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "All three advice structures are followed by an infinitive (comer, beber, evitar…), never a conjugated form."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:learn:ecc836f7', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "How do I say what I am going to change?", "reading": "<p>Use the near future — <strong>voy a</strong> + <strong>infinitive</strong> — to state a plan or intention:</p>\n            <ul>\n              <li><span data-say=\"Voy a comer más verduras.\">Voy a comer más verduras.</span> — I am going to eat more vegetables.</li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"Voy a evitar la comida rápida.\">Voy a evitar la comida rápida.</span> — I am going to avoid fast food.</li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"Voy a beber menos azúcar.\">Voy a beber menos azúcar.</span> — I am going to have less sugar.</li>\n            </ul>\n            <p><strong>evitar</strong> = to avoid, <strong>la comida rápida</strong> = fast food. Add a time phrase to extend: <span data-say=\"todos los días\">todos los días</span> (every day), <span data-say=\"a menudo\">a menudo</span> (often).</p>", "question": "How do you say ‘I am going to avoid fast food’?", "options": ["Voy a evitar la comida rápida", "Se debe evitar la comida rápida", "Evito la comida rápida", "Hay que evitar la comida rápida"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "voy a + infinitive = a future plan; ‘I am going to avoid’ = Voy a evitar."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:learn:3933554d', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "How do I give opinions and reasons?", "reading": "<p>Opinions lift your mark. Use <strong>gustar</strong>-type verbs and join ideas with connectors:</p>\n            <ul>\n              <li><span data-say=\"Me gusta la fruta.\">Me gusta la fruta.</span> — I like fruit. <em>(singular thing)</em></li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"Me gustan las verduras.\">Me gustan las verduras.</span> — I like vegetables. <em>(plural → gusta<strong>n</strong>)</em></li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"Prefiero el pescado.\">Prefiero el pescado.</span> — I prefer fish.</li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>Connectors: <span data-say=\"porque\">porque</span> (because), <span data-say=\"pero\">pero</span> (but), <span data-say=\"también\">también</span> (also). Example: <span data-say=\"Me gusta la carne, pero no como carne todos los días porque es mala para la salud.\">Me gusta la carne, pero no como carne todos los días porque es mala para la salud.</span></p>", "question": "Why is it ‘Me gustan las verduras’ (not ‘gusta’)?", "options": ["verduras is plural, so the verb agrees", "it expresses a future plan, not a preference", "verduras is a feminine singular noun here", "it is simply someone’s opinion"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "gustar agrees with the THING liked; verduras is plural → gustan (nothing to do with plans or opinions)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:learn:0e35c440', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Higher: reach for the top band", "reading": "<p><span class=\"tier-h\">H</span> To push into the higher band, add a <strong>conditional</strong> recommendation and a <strong>concession</strong>:</p>\n            <ul>\n              <li><span data-say=\"Se debería reducir el azúcar.\">Se debería reducir el azúcar.</span> — One <em>should</em> reduce sugar. <span class=\"tier-h\">H</span></li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"Lo más importante es llevar una dieta variada.\">Lo más importante es llevar una dieta variada.</span> — The most important thing is to have a varied diet. <span class=\"tier-h\">H</span></li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"Aunque me gusta el chocolate, intento comer sano.\">Aunque me gusta el chocolate, intento comer sano.</span> — Although I like chocolate, I try to eat healthily. <span class=\"tier-h\">H</span></li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>Aim for: <strong>opinion + reason + connector + a second tense</strong> in one sentence.</p>", "question": "Which sentence shows a typically Higher-tier feature?", "options": ["Se debería reducir el azúcar", "Me gusta mucho la fruta fresca del país", "Como pan casi todos los días", "Bebo bastante agua con las comidas"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘se debería’ is a conditional — a Higher feature. Option B is longer but only present-tense opinion."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:misc:d583c1b6', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'misc', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Misconception check", "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Me gusta las verduras.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Me gustan las verduras.</p>", "question": "Why is it ‘Me gustan las verduras’?", "options": ["verduras is plural, so it becomes gustan", "the subject ‘yo’ is what forces the ending gustan here", "verduras is a masculine noun", "the sentence is in the past"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "gustar agrees with the thing liked (verduras, plural) → gustan. It is NOT the person that drives the ending — that is the classic error."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet:misc:230b261d', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-1-food-drink-and-a-balanced-diet', '2.1 Food, Drink and a Balanced Diet', 'misc', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Misconception check", "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> una dieta equilibrado</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> una dieta equilibrada</p>", "question": "Why must it be ‘equilibrada’?", "options": ["the adjective agrees with the feminine noun ‘dieta’", "it copies the gender of whichever verb happens to be closest to it", "the masculine form is the safe default", "adjectives only change in the plural"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Adjectives agree with their noun in gender AND number: dieta is feminine singular → equilibrada."}'::jsonb),
