('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:learn:6a64d7bc', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "How do I talk about exercise and sport?", "reading": "<p>The key verb is <span data-say=\"hacer ejercicio\">hacer ejercicio</span> (to do exercise / to work out). Here is the core vocabulary — tap 🔊 to hear each one.</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"el deporte\">el deporte</span></td><td>sport</td><td><span data-say=\"correr\">correr</span></td><td>to run</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"nadar\">nadar</span></td><td>to swim</td><td><span data-say=\"montar en bicicleta\">montar en bicicleta</span></td><td>to cycle</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"el gimnasio\">el gimnasio</span></td><td>the gym</td><td><span data-say=\"entrenar\">entrenar</span></td><td>to train</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"estar en forma\">estar en forma</span></td><td>to be fit</td><td><span data-say=\"activo\">activo / activa</span></td><td>active</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p>Model sentence: <span data-say=\"Para estar en forma, hago ejercicio tres veces por semana.\">Para estar en forma, hago ejercicio tres veces por semana.</span> — <em>To be fit, I exercise three times a week.</em></p>", "question": "What does ‘estar en forma’ mean?", "options": ["to be fit", "to run a race", "to go to the gym building", "to fill in a paper form"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "estar en forma = to be fit / in shape. It is a false friend — ‘forma’ here is not a paper ‘form’."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:learn:70ccf269', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "How do I say what hurts? (me duele / me duelen)", "reading": "<p>To say something hurts, use <strong>doler</strong> — and it behaves <em>exactly like</em> <strong>gustar</strong>: the verb agrees with the body part, not with you.</p>\n            <ul>\n              <li>ONE thing hurts → <span data-say=\"me duele\">me duele</span>: <span data-say=\"Me duele la cabeza.\">Me duele la cabeza.</span> (My head hurts.)</li>\n              <li>MORE THAN ONE → <span data-say=\"me duelen\">me duelen</span>: <span data-say=\"Me duelen los pies.\">Me duelen los pies.</span> (My feet hurt.)</li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>Body parts (<strong>el cuerpo</strong>):</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"la cabeza\">la cabeza</span></td><td>head</td><td><span data-say=\"el estómago\">el estómago</span></td><td>stomach</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"la garganta\">la garganta</span></td><td>throat</td><td><span data-say=\"la espalda\">la espalda</span></td><td>back</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"las piernas\">las piernas</span></td><td>legs</td><td><span data-say=\"los ojos\">los ojos</span></td><td>eyes</td></tr>\n            </table>", "question": "Why is it ‘Me duelen los pies’ and not ‘Me duele los pies’?", "options": ["‘los pies’ is plural, so the verb is plural", "‘doler’ is a verb that is always plural in Spanish", "‘pies’ is a masculine noun", "it describes a future plan"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Like gustar, doler agrees with the body part; ‘los pies’ is plural → duelen (doler is NOT always plural)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:learn:b37586a3', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "How do I describe health problems?", "reading": "<p>Use <strong>estar</strong> (a temporary state) for how you feel:</p>\n            <ul>\n              <li><span data-say=\"estar enfermo\">estar enfermo / enferma</span> — to be ill</li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"estar cansado\">estar cansado / cansada</span> — to be tired</li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"estar resfriado\">estar resfriado / resfriada</span> — to have a cold</li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"el estrés\">el estrés</span> — stress; <span data-say=\"estar estresado\">estar estresado</span> — to be stressed</li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>Example: <span data-say=\"Estoy muy cansado porque no duermo bien.\">Estoy muy cansado porque no duermo bien.</span> — <em>I am very tired because I don’t sleep well.</em></p>", "question": "Which verb do you use for ‘I am tired’ — a temporary state?", "options": ["estar → estoy cansado", "ser → soy cansado", "tener → tengo cansado", "hacer → hago cansado"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Temporary states and feelings use estar: estoy cansado. ‘ser’ would describe a permanent trait."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:learn:de0ddfe8', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "How do I give health advice?", "reading": "<p>Reuse the advice structures from 2.1 — each is followed by an <strong>infinitive</strong>:</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"se debe descansar\">se debe descansar</span></td><td>one should rest</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"no se debe fumar\">no se debe fumar</span></td><td>one must not smoke</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"hay que dormir ocho horas\">hay que dormir ocho horas</span></td><td>you have to sleep eight hours</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"deberías relajarte\">deberías relajarte</span> <span class=\"tier-h\">H</span></td><td>you should relax</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p>Example: <span data-say=\"Para evitar el estrés, se debe descansar y hacer ejercicio.\">Para evitar el estrés, se debe descansar y hacer ejercicio.</span></p>", "question": "What follows ‘se debe’, ‘hay que’ and ‘deberías’?", "options": ["an infinitive (descansar, dormir…)", "a verb conjugated in the preterite past tense", "an adjective that agrees", "a noun on its own"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "All the advice structures take an infinitive."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:learn:148f189a', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "How do I talk about bad habits?", "reading": "<p>Common ‘malos hábitos’ (bad habits) and how to reject them:</p>\n            <ul>\n              <li><span data-say=\"fumar\">fumar</span> — to smoke; <span data-say=\"el tabaco\">el tabaco</span> — tobacco</li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"beber alcohol\">beber alcohol</span> — to drink alcohol; <span data-say=\"las drogas\">las drogas</span> — drugs</li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"dejar de fumar\">dejar de + infinitive</span> — to stop doing something: <span data-say=\"dejar de fumar\">dejar de fumar</span> (to stop smoking)</li>\n            </ul>\n            <p><span data-say=\"No se debe fumar porque es muy malo para la salud.\">No se debe fumar porque es muy malo para la salud.</span></p>", "question": "‘dejar de fumar’ means…", "options": ["to stop smoking", "to let others smoke", "to smoke a little more", "to enjoy smoking outside"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "dejar de + infinitive = to stop doing something; dejar de fumar = to stop smoking."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:learn:4e0e98dd', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Higher: reflexives and future plans", "reading": "<p><span class=\"tier-h\">H</span> Many health verbs are <strong>reflexive</strong> — the action is done to yourself, so they take <strong>me / te / se</strong>:</p>\n            <ul>\n              <li><span data-say=\"relajarse\">relajarse</span> → <span data-say=\"me relajo\">me relajo</span> (I relax)</li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"acostarse\">acostarse</span> → <span data-say=\"me acuesto temprano\">me acuesto temprano</span> (I go to bed early)</li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>Combine with a plan or a conditional for the top band:</p>\n            <ul>\n              <li><span data-say=\"Voy a dejar de fumar y acostarme más temprano.\">Voy a dejar de fumar y acostarme más temprano.</span> <span class=\"tier-h\">H</span></li>\n              <li><span data-say=\"Se debería evitar el estrés para mantenerse sano.\">Se debería evitar el estrés para mantenerse sano.</span> <span class=\"tier-h\">H</span></li>\n            </ul>", "question": "Which sentence correctly uses a reflexive verb?", "options": ["Me acuesto temprano", "Acuesto temprano cada noche", "Yo acuesto muy temprano", "Se acuesto temprano"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "acostarse is reflexive: (yo) me acuesto. Dropping ‘me’ or using the wrong pronoun is wrong."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:misc:05500ed6', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'misc', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Misconception check", "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Me duele los pies.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Me duelen los pies.</p>", "question": "Why is ‘Me duele los pies’ wrong?", "options": ["‘los pies’ is plural, so it must be ‘duelen’", "you must always put the verb ‘estar’ in front of it", "‘pies’ needs a written accent", "the pronoun should be ‘te’, not ‘me’"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "doler agrees with the body part; plural body part → duelen."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:misc:255a1152', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'misc', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Misconception check", "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Estoy constipado. (= I am constipated)</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Estoy constipado. (= I have a cold)</p>", "question": "What does ‘constipado’ really mean?", "options": ["having a cold", "being constipated as you would guess", "feeling completely healthy", "being extremely tired"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Classic false friend: constipado = having a cold."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:misc:55a52a3c', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'misc', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Misconception check", "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Soy cansado.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Estoy cansado.</p>", "question": "Why ‘Estoy cansado’, not ‘Soy cansado’?", "options": ["tiredness is a temporary state → estar", "you should always use ‘tener’ with any feeling", "‘cansado’ is a plural adjective", "‘ser’ is only for the past"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Temporary states and moods take estar; ser would mean it is a permanent trait."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:misc:a6bf4f90', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'misc', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Misconception check", "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Acuesto temprano.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Me acuesto temprano.</p>", "question": "What is missing in ‘Acuesto temprano’?", "options": ["the reflexive pronoun ‘me’ (me acuesto)", "an accent on the final letter of the verb form", "the linking word ‘a’", "the article ‘la’"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "acostarse is reflexive: you need me/te/se — ‘me acuesto’."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:misc:707feafe', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'misc', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Misconception check", "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Se debe fumar para relajarse.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> No se debe fumar; se debe descansar para relajarse.</p>", "question": "Why is the ‘wrong’ sentence a problem?", "options": ["it recommends smoking, which is bad advice", "it is missing an infinitive after ‘se debe’", "‘relajarse’ is spelt incorrectly", "it uses the past tense by mistake"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "The grammar is fine, but the ADVICE is wrong — smoking is malo para la salud."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:tips:faad4787', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'tips', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "tip — Paper 1 — Dictation (listening)", "reading": "Health sentences reuse chunks you know: ‘me duele…’, ‘se debe…’, ‘voy a…’. Listen for whether it is ‘duele’ (one thing) or ‘duelen’ (more than one) — the ending tells you if the body part is singular or plural.", "question": "You hear ‘…duelen…’. What does that tell you?", "options": ["more than one body part hurts", "only one single body part is actually hurting", "nothing hurts at all", "it is a future plan"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "The -n ending of ‘duelen’ signals a plural body part (los pies, las piernas…)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:tips:ac92db52', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'tips', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "tip — Paper 3 — Translation into English", "reading": "Watch the false friends: ‘constipado’ = having a cold, ‘estar en forma’ = to be fit. Keep ‘me duele la cabeza’ natural: ‘my head hurts’ / ‘I have a headache’, not ‘the head hurts me’.", "question": "‘Estoy resfriado y me duele la garganta’ =", "options": ["I have a cold and my throat hurts", "I am stressed out and my whole back hurts", "I am tired and my head hurts", "I am fit and my legs hurt"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "resfriado = having a cold; la garganta = throat."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:tips:2f1a4fab', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'tips', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "evaluate — Paper 4 — Writing & translation into Spanish", "reading": "Combine a problem, advice and a plan: ‘Estoy estresado, así que se debe descansar y voy a acostarme más temprano.’ At Higher, add a reflexive and a conditional: ‘se debería…’, ‘relajarse’.", "question": "Which answer reaches the top band?", "options": ["Estoy estresado, así que voy a descansar y acostarme más temprano", "Estoy muy estresado y estresado y cansado todos los días sin parar nunca", "Estoy mal", "Me duele todo"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "It links a problem, a plan, a reflexive and a time phrase — range and accuracy, not just length."}'::jsonb),
